Artist: Simon Dominic Song: 넌 언제나 (You Always) (Feat. GRAY & Hoody) Album: Two Yoo Project - Sugarman Part.23

  HOODY THO. For...
posts.track_name: 넌 언제나 (You Always) (Prod. by GRAY, Feat. GRAY & Hoody)
posts.caption:
Artist: Simon Dominic
Song: 넌 언제나 (You Always) (Feat. GRAY & Hoody)
Album: Two Yoo Project - Sugarman Part.23

HOODY THO. For those who don’t know, “Two Yoo Project - Sugarman” is a tv show that focuses on reworking one-hit wonders into songs that would appeal to the current music market. Gray’s production on this version of Mono’s “넌 언제나” sounds absolutely amazing and the way he sampled the vocals reminds me of how Kanye sampled Chaka Khan on his track “Through The Wire”. What really hooked me though was Hoody’s voice from the first verse on. She is a damn goddess.

Live performance.

posts.summary:
Artist: DEAN Song: I Love It (feat. Dok2) Album: Single (I Love It)

  In anticipation for Dok2′s upcoming track “Bad Vibes...
posts.caption:
Artist: DEAN
Song: I Love It (feat. Dok2)
Album: Single (I Love It)

In anticipation for Dok2′s upcoming track “Bad Vibes Lonely (Feat. DEAN)” dropping March 28, I’ve decided to feature their previous collab: “I Love It”. Three reasons why I’m pumped for the new single: 1. I like Dok2′s slower songs when he’s not rapping about his money and tryna be “hard” (ie: Lonely Nights). 2. Good Vibes Only was a good song and I like the play on words. 3. DEAN … dude has been everywhere lately and been killin’ the r&b scene (ps: his new album “TRBL” is slated to be released on March 25).

Anyways, ‘I Love It’ is a pure sex. I recently looked up the lyrics and they’re pretty sensual but they also seem pretty specific…who you singing ‘bout Dean??. “I love it and I like it, your short hair, even the freckles underneath your eyes.” (TMI: I once met a Korean girl from NYC with freckles and I thought they were the CUTEST thing ever…)
